title: Second Largest Element
description: Finding the largest element is common, but finding the second largest requires a bit more logic. In this problem, you are given an array of integers. Your task is to find and print the second largest distinct element in the array. If the array contains duplicates, they should not affect the ranking (e.g., in [10, 10, 5], the second largest is 5).
input_format: A single line containing space-separated integers.
output_format: Output a single integer representing the second largest element in the array.
